<DOC><DOCNO> AP890923-0020 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-23-89 0321EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Norway-Extremist     09-23 0167</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Norway-Extremist,0170</SECOND><HEAD>Anti-Immigration Leader Convicted For Bomb Plot</HEAD><DATELINE>ARENDAL, Norway (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A founder of an anti-immigration group wasconvicted of plotting to bomb a refugee center and sentenced to oneyear in prison, news reports said.   Arne Myrdal, 53, called his conviction on Friday ``absurd'' and``a political judgment,'' according to the Norwegian news agencyNTB. He was expected to appeal.   The Agder Country Court said evidence, including dynamite and ahand-drawn map of a new refugee reception center near this southernNorway town, proved that Myrdal intended to bomb the center, NTBreported.   Myrdal helped found the People's Movement Against Immigration inOctober 1987, after the annual number of asylum seekers in Norwayincreased tenfold in two years to about 8,600 people.   A second defendant in the case, Fred Skauen, 34, was convicted ofconspiracy and threatening to kill a police informer who acted as aprosecution witness, the news report said. He was sentenced to eightmonths in prison, according to the report.</TEXT></DOC>